ufflet}}{{MSP|628|Braviary}}{{MSP|661|Fletchling}}{{MSP|662|Fletchinder}}{{MSP|663|Talonflame}}{{MSP|714|Noibat}}<br>{{MSP|715|Noivern}}|Tailwind|Flying|Status|&mdash;|&mdash;|15}}\n{{learnlist/breedf/7|Noivern|Flying|Dragon|6}}\n\n====By [[Move Tutor|tutoring]]====\n{{learnlist/tutorh/7|Noivern|Flying|Dragon|6}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Defog|Flying|Status|—|—|15|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Draco Meteor|Dragon|Special|130|90|5||\'\'\'|yes|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Dragon Pulse|Dragon|Special|85|100|10||\'\'\'|no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Heat Wave|Fire|Special|95|90|10|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Hyper Voice|Normal|Special|90|100|10|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Iron Tail|Steel|Physical|100|75|15|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Laser Focus|Normal|Status|—|—|30|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Outrage|Dragon|Physical|120|100|10||\'\'\'|no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Sky Attack|Flying|Physical|140|90|5||\'\'\'|no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Snatch|Dark|Status|—|—|10|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Snore|Normal|Special|50|100|15|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Super Fang|Normal|Physical|—|90|10|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Tailwind|Flying|Status|—|—|15|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Uproar|Normal|Special|90|100|10|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutor7|Water Pulse|Water|Special|60|100|20|||no|yes}}\n{{learnlist/tutorf/7|Noivern|Flying|Dragon|6}}\n\n====By a prior [[evolution]]====\n{{learnlist/prevoh/7|Noivern|Flying|Dragon|6}}\n{{learnlist/prevo7null}}\n{{learnlist/prevof/7|Noivern|Flying|Dragon|6}}\n\n===Side game data===\n{{Spindata/Head|type=Flying|type2=Dragon}}\n{{Spindata/Battle Trozei|col=6|type=Flying|ndex=715\n|power=2\n}}\n|-\n{{Spindata/Shuffle|col=6|type=Flying|ndex=715|num=488\n|min=70\n|max=125\n|raisemaxlevel=10\n|skill=Cloud Clear++\n|skilldesc=Sometimes clears away five black-cloud disruptions.\n|swapper=Shot Out\n}}\n|}\n\n===Evolution===\n{{evobox-2\n|pictype=art\n|type1=Flying\n|type2=Dragon\n|no1=714\n|name1=Noibat\n|type1-1=Flying\n|type2-1=Dragon\n|evo1={{bag|Rare Candy}}<br>{{color2|000|Level|Level 48}}\n|no2=715\n|name2=Noivern\n|type1-2=Flying\n|type2-2=Dragon}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=flying|type2=dragon}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=715}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=715}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|715|Noivern}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Noivern can be seen as a parallel to {{p|Crobat}}. Both are {{type|Flying}} Pokémon based on bats that have {{a|Infiltrator}} as a possible [[Ability]]. They have the same base stat total and the same base {{stat|HP}}, {{stat|Defense}}, and {{stat|Special Defense}}.\n* Noivern\'s {{pmin|Germany|German}} name, UHaFnir, consists of both more than two capitalized Latin letters and doesn\'t have a dash.\n\n===Origin===\nNoivern seems to be based on a combination of {{wp|wyvern}}, a {{wp|Plecotus|long-eared bat}}, {{wp|Pteropus|fruit bat}}, or a {{wp|Phyllostomidae|leaf-nosed bat}}, and {{wp|loudspeaker}} or {{wp|tweeter}}. Inspiration for its design may also have been drawn from gargoyles.\n\n====Name origin====\nNoivern may be a combination of \'\'noise\'\' and \'\'{{wp|wyvern}}\'\'.\n\nOnvern may be a combination of 音 \'\'on\'\' (sound), 音波 \'\'onpa\'\' (sound wave), and ワイバーン \'\'wyvern\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Flying|type2=Dragon\n|ja=オンバーン \'\'Onvern\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|音 \'\'on\'\'|sound}}, {{tt|音波 \'\'onpa\'\'|sound wave}}, and \'\'wyvern\'\'\n|fr=Bruyverne |frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|bruit|noise}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|wyverne|wyvern}}\n|es=Noivern |esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=UHaFnir |demeaning=From \'\'{{wp|UHF}}\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Fafnir}}\n|it=Noivern |itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=음번 \'\'Eumbeon\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|음 (音) \'\'eum\'\'|sound}} and \'\'wyvern\'\'\n|zh_yue=音波飛龍 \'\'Yāmbōfēilùhng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|音波 \'\'yāmbō\'\'|sound wave}} and {{tt|飛龍 \'\'fēilùhng\'\'|wyvern}}\n|zh_cmn=音波龍 \'\'Yīnbōlóng \'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|音波 \'\'yīnbō \'\'|sound wave}} and {{tt|龍 \'\'lóng \'\'|dragon}}\n|hi=नोईवेर्न \